# Git branches and commits

## Branches

Use short, descriptive names with **no** `cursor/` or other tooling prefix.

Examples: `katas-layout-and-agent-plan`, `evening-news-godot-scaffold`

Ignore diff-tab or automation defaults that suggest a `cursor/` prefix.

## Commits

Start commit message subjects with a **lowercase** letter. Match existing style (`update kata table`, `new incubator item: …`).

## Pull requests

**The diff is the review.** The author reads diffs; do not duplicate diff content as a test plan.

### Test plan — when to include

| PR type | Test plan |
|---------|-----------|
| Docs, layout, specs, rules, skills | **Omit** — or one line: `N/A — review diff` |
| Godot / runtime / GameLauncher integration | **Only** steps that require running something the diff cannot show |

### Test plan — allowed (runtime only)

Things a diff cannot prove:

- [ ] `:composeApp:run` — home screen loads
- [ ] Gym station X: throw physics feels correct
- [ ] Exported build launches from GameLauncher and exits cleanly

### Test plan — never include

- Re-read files the diff already shows (`verify PLAN.md says katas/`)
- `rg` / grep / lint checks (that's CI or the diff)
- `.gitignore` / `.cursorignore` spot-checks
- "Confirm intent matches" / "merge when happy"
- Per-file checkbox audits of markdown we just wrote

If there is nothing to run, **leave Test plan out entirely.**
